00:15:27,998 --> 00:15:30,482
how much say do you have in things like item and weapon descriptions,

212
00:15:30,822 --> 00:15:34,207
or anything that could be considered systemic that adds to the narrative as a whole?

213
00:15:35,695 --> 00:15:39,377
So at Obsidian, we do try to, you know, and this is different at every studio.

214
00:15:40,757 --> 00:15:44,538
I should also say that at Obsidian, narrative designers and writers are the same role.

215
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:46,239
Many studios separate them out.

216
00:15:46,299 --> 00:15:46,719
We do not.

217
00:15:47,939 --> 00:15:52,621
We try to integrate a narrative pretty early in our process because, you know,

218
00:15:52,641 --> 00:15:57,142
again, it's, it's really just about making sure that we have a, a world that feels

219
00:15:57,202 --> 00:15:58,223
cohesive and.

220
00:15:58,717 --> 00:16:02,999
you know, a story that feels reflective of the game the player is actually playing.

221
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:08,322
So, you know, narrative designers will tend to have a lot more,

222
00:16:09,323 --> 00:16:14,105
a lot more authorial control over anything that is like a quest item

223
00:16:14,525 --> 00:16:17,187
or, you know, obviously a note or a readable in world.

224
00:16:18,307 --> 00:16:21,309
We aren't always quite as closely involved with, you know,

225
00:16:21,349 --> 00:16:23,770
things like weapon descriptions,

226
00:16:24,290 --> 00:16:26,211
especially the stuff that is a bit more systemic.

227
00:16:26,672 --> 00:16:30,494
That's the kind of thing where it honestly just sort of depends on your staffing where

228
00:16:31,054 --> 00:16:34,176
you might have your narrative designers do a pass on that stuff later, but

229
00:16:34,596 --> 00:16:40,820
because it is a bit less closely tied to quest content that the player is likely to be playing,

230
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:47,924
it's not quite as necessary to have a really detailed writing pass on this particular sword.

