00:25:40,987 --> 00:25:45,389
Like I, I do think it's important, you know, as, as a writer, honestly, as, as

360
00:25:45,429 --> 00:25:50,631
a designer of any kind in games, as a, as a creator in any kind of media, um, to

361
00:25:51,072 --> 00:25:55,774
consume widely, you know, don't just play games also read books and watch movies.

362
00:25:55,974 --> 00:26:01,037
And don't just, you know, play the genre you make, like try other things as well.

363
00:26:01,657 --> 00:26:06,019
Um, I do think it's important to, you know, kind of get outside of a very narrow

364
00:26:06,059 --> 00:26:07,320
lane and, you know,

365
00:26:08,457 --> 00:26:14,380
draw inspiration from and experience the variety and the options that other media and other genres

366
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:24,344
offer you. I get inspired by great characters and by really evocative settings. And so, for me,

367
00:26:24,745 --> 00:26:30,667
finding works of fiction that offer me those things keeps me creatively engaged.

368
00:26:32,102 --> 00:26:36,766
Gotcha. We're going to close out with our last question for the day coming from Kirstie Logan Fowler.

